However ABC has reported that a search of Tsarnaev’s home after the bombings was focused on finding clothing consistent with what was shown on a security video from the Macy's store where the cookers were bought.

Russell could face charges of misprision of a felony, or failing to notify authorities of a crime about to happen. 

Tamerlan Tsarnaev also bought $200 worth of fireworks from a store in New Hampshire, including 48 mortar shells, some of which were used in the bombs.

He was killed in a police shootout three days after the attack. 

Dzhokhar Tsarnaev, his brother and Russell's brother-in-law, is currently awaiting federal trial for the unthinkable attack.

The two-month process to select a jury for the trial was completed Tuesday, authorities said, a day before opening statements in the long-awaited case are to begin.

